TITLE:
      Weight Gain Prevention
SUMMARY:
      The specific aim of the proposed project is to test two separate self-regulation
      interventions to prevent weight gain in young adults, one based on making sustained small
      changes in behavior to prevent weight gain and the other on making periodic larger behavior
      changes resulting in weight loss.
ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA:
      Inclusion Criteria:
          -  Age 18-35
          -  Body mass index between 23 and 30
          -  Interested in preventing weight gain
        Exclusion Criteria:
          -  BMI outside of range specified
          -  Age outside of range specified
          -  History of or current eating disorder or substance abuse
          -  Recent weight loss greater than 5% of weight
          -  Currently in another research study that would interfere
